4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING JOB GROWTH INCENTIVE TAX CREDITS TO
5 INCLUDE CERTAIN APPRENTICES IN THE CONSTRUCTION INDUSTRY; REVISING THE DEFINITION OF
6 "QUALIFYING NEW EMPLOYEE" TO INCLUDE AN APPRENTICE; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 15-31-175
7 AND 39-11-404, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 15-31-175, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "15-31-175. (Temporary) Grow Montana jobs -- annual job growth incentive tax credit. (1) There
13 is an annual job growth incentive tax credit against the taxes otherwise due under 15-31-121 or 15-31-122 that
14 is allowable in the amount established pursuant to 15-30-2361 when a taxpayer hires qualifying new employees
15 as defined in 39-11-404 in the state. The credit is administered as provided in 15-30-2361, 39-11-404, and this
16 section.
17 (2) If the credit allowed under this section is claimed by a small business corporation as defined in
18 15-30-3301 or a partnership, the credit must be attributed to shareholders or partners using the same
19 proportion to report the corporation's or partnership's income or loss for Montana income tax purposes.
20 (Terminates December 31, 2028--sec. 4, Ch. 391, L. 2023.)"
21
22 Section 2. Section 39-11-404, MCA, is amended to read:
23 "39-11-404. (Temporary) Employer job growth incentive tax credit -- administration. (1) An
24 employer that hires qualifying new employees is eligible for an annual job growth incentive tax credit against
25 income taxes imposed pursuant to Title 15, chapter 30 or 31.
26 (2) The amount and duration of the credit is administered by the department of revenue as
27 provided in 15-30-2361 and 15-31-175.
28 (3) A qualifying employer seeking approval to claim a credit shall apply for a credit certificate with
